transcription.text:
Speaker 1: My name is Javier Duque and then I call in to do a cancellation of a purchase I did about—

Speaker 2: I think that was last weekend.

Speaker 1: Okay, I can help you with that, sir.

Speaker 2: One moment.

Speaker 1: You said Javier, correct?

Speaker 2: Javier, yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, one moment.

Speaker 2: All right, Javier, so I do have you pulled up here.

Speaker 1: I do notice you did place an order.

Speaker 2: What's going on?

Speaker 1: Why don't you want the order anymore?

Speaker 2: No, I don't want it because, you know, I need to do a series of medical tests before—

Speaker 1: to do it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, no, sir, this is prescribed by a doctor, so...

Speaker 1: No, no, I have to do a couple of other things, cardiologic problems.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, you know, you can always just take your time and return this and handle—

Speaker 1: that.

Speaker 2: It's a 90-day return policy.

Speaker 1: Well, I want to cancel right now.

Speaker 2: No, I do understand that, sir.

Speaker 1: I mean, obviously, we can do that for you, but, I mean, you already ordered this and—

Speaker 2: I do understand you want to go check some things out, but you can have time to check—

Speaker 1: things out and still get your order.

Speaker 2: Sorry, did you send the order already?

Speaker 1: Yes, the order was, I believe it was shipped out.

Speaker 2: Yeah, it was shipped out on the 24th.

Speaker 1: So how can I do in order to return it?

Speaker 2: How do you want to return it?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I don't need it because I need to do a series of neurologic and cardiologic tests—

Speaker 2: before to start to take that medicine.

Speaker 1: I mean, I do understand and, you know, a doctor obviously prescribed this to you, so, I mean—

Speaker 2: they know better than we do, but you can take your time and check those things out.

Speaker 1: So you have 90 days to go do your tests or whatever you need to do.

Speaker 2: You can always return this.

Speaker 1: Well, that's my question.

Speaker 2: You said that that product was shipped already?

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: Okay, so now, at the moment I receive this product at my place, how can I return it?

Speaker 1: You would just put return to sender on the package, sir.

Speaker 2: Say it again?

Speaker 1: Return to sender on the package.

Speaker 2: Okay, and then the refund, how is it made effective?

Speaker 1: We will refund it for you.

Speaker 2: You understand you can order this as needed, correct?

Speaker 1: Yeah, but I don't need it because what we need to do, I need to do a series of neurologic—

Speaker 2: tests before to start to take the medicine because the doctor said I have hypotension—

Speaker 1: and then that's not going to help me.

Speaker 2: And you did provide us with that information when you ordered this, correct?

Speaker 1: No, I didn't know because I went yesterday.

Speaker 2: Okay, all right, well, yeah, just put return to sender on it when you get it and I'll send—

Speaker 1: it back to us and the refund—

Speaker 2: will get processed for you.

Speaker 1: Okay, so you said, sir, that the product was shipped already to my place, to my address.

Speaker 2: As soon as I get it, I can return it to the address there, right?

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: Well, thank you so much.

Speaker 1: What is your name, sir?

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.
